# GTM-CC: DB-Powered Campaign System

## Role Detection (ALWAYS DO THIS FIRST)

At the **start of every conversation**, ask:

> "Who am I working with today?
> 1. **Kuldeep** — Clay Operator
> 2. **Hasan** — Campaign Operator
> 3. **Mayank** — Strategist
>
> Type your name or role number."

Once identified, enforce that role's permissions for the entire session.

After identifying, show their available workflows:
- **Clay Operator:** "pull leads", "push to clay", "check batch", "export csv"
- **Campaign Operator:** "get batch", "check outputs", "reuse emails"
- **Strategist:** All of the above + "create recipe", "test recipe", "review performance"

---

## System Overview

- **1 Neon PostgreSQL database** (connected via Neon MCP)
- **5 tables:** clients, segments, leads, recipes, email_outputs
- **3 roles** with different permissions
- **Clay integration:** Webhook push (Neon → Clay) + 3 HTTP columns push-back (Clay → Neon)

---

## Database Schema (v3.1)

### clients
client_id (UUID PK), client_name, client_website, client_status (active/paused/churned), target_icp_details, target_persona, pain_points, client_usp_differentiators, approved (boolean)

### segments
segment_id (serial PK), client_id (FK), segment_name, segment_tag, status (active/paused/archived)

### leads
lead_id (serial PK), email (UNIQUE), first_name, last_name, full_name, job_title, linkedin_profile_url, company_name, company_domain, company_website, industry, monthly_visits (int), employee_count (text), email_verified (text), email_verified_at, is_catchall, mx_provider, lcp (float), tti (float), aov (float), **segment_ids (int[])**, info_tags (text[]), extra_data (jsonb)

### recipes
recipe_id (serial PK), client_id (FK), segment_id (FK), version (int), status (active/inactive/testing), approach_content, value_prop, clay_instructions

### email_outputs
output_id (serial PK), lead_id (FK), client_id (FK), segment_id (FK), recipe_id (FK), recipe_version, selected_approach, subject_line_1, subject_line_2, email_1_variant_a/b/c, email_2_variant_a/b/c, email_3_variant_a/b/c, company_summary, batch_id

---

## Permissions Matrix

| Action | Strategist | Clay Operator | Campaign Operator |
|--------|-----------|---------------|-------------------|
| SELECT any table | Yes | Yes | Yes |
| INSERT/UPDATE clients | Yes | No | No |
| INSERT/UPDATE segments | Yes | No | No |
| UPDATE leads (enrichment) | Yes | Yes | No |
| INSERT/UPDATE recipes | Yes | No | No |
| INSERT email_outputs | Yes | Yes (via Clay) | No |
| Export CSV | Yes | Yes | Yes |
| Push to Clay webhook | Yes | Yes | No |
| Free-form SQL | Yes | No | No |

---

## How to Use This System

When the operator wants to do something, guide them step-by-step. Always ASK before executing. The key workflows are described in the other rule files. Use the Neon MCP to query the database directly.

For any database query, prefer using the Neon MCP tools. If MCP is unavailable, fall back to `scripts/db.py`.
